ing the opening ceremony was [[John Tsang]], [[Financial Secretary (Hong Kong)|Financial Secretary of the Hong Kong SAR]]. He said during his opening note that Taiwan and Hong Kong have made substantial progress in the area of economic exchanges, cultural exchanges, financial supervision cooperation, bilateral transportation arrangement and cargo transshipment.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/>\n\n==List of Directors==\n\n# [[John Leung]] (7 December 2011 \u2013 11 August 2015)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hketco.hk/en/welcome/cv/index.html |title=Hketco - Cv |publisher=Hketco.hk |date=2011-12-07 |accessdate=2014-04-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328011605/http://www.hketco.hk/en/welcome/cv/index.html |archivedate=2014-03-28 }}</ref>\n# [[Rex Chang]] (12 August 2015 \u2013 28 July 2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ejinsight.com/20180907-why-is-hk-delaying-work-visa-for-taiwan-agency-official/|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n==Transportation==\nThe office is accessible within walking distance south of [[Taipei City Hall Station]] of the [[Taipei Metro]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[Taiwan\u2013Hong Kong Economic and Cultural Co-operation Council]]\n* [[Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office]]\n* [[Foreign relations of Hong Kong]]\n* [[Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Hong Kong]]\n* [[List of diplomatic missions in Taiwan]]\n* [[Cross-Strait relations]]\n* [[One-China policy]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Diplomatic missions in the Republic of China}}\n\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Diplomatic missions in Taipei]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan relations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name                 = Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office\n| native_name          = \n| native_name_a        = \u9999\u6e2f\u7d93\u6fdf\u8cbf\u6613\u6587\u5316\u8fa6\u4e8b\u8655\n| native_name_r        = \n| type   